        <heading>2129.  Assignment of errors unnecessary; exception</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2129.  Assignment of errors unnecessary; exception
An assignment of errors is not necessary in any appeal.  Where the appellant designates only portions of the record as the record on appeal, he must serve with his designation a concise statement of the points on which he intends to rely, and the appeal shall be limited to those points.</p>
        </content>
